6.  Section Transformation Mapping:

    This section defines how traditional resume sections MUST be transformed
    into RFC-compliant sections.

    6.1 METADATA Section Transformation:

        - The METADATA section MUST be retained as the document header.
        - RFC field MUST be set to: RESUME-RFC-000000
        - GROUP field MUST be set to: PROFESSIONAL PROFILE
        - TITLE field MUST be set to: BACKEND ENGINEER PROFILE
        - ACRONYM field MUST be set to: RBENG
        - AUTHOR field MUST contain: RICHEVE BEBEDOR <richeve.bebedor+vs-work@gmail.com>
        - CATEGORY field MUST be set to: INFORMATIONAL
        - STATUS field MUST be set to: DRAFT
        - VERSION field MUST be set to: 000000 (0.0.0)
        - CREATED field MUST contain the creation date in YYYY-MM-DD format.
        - CHECKSUM field MUST be set to: <SHA-256>

    6.2 Summary Section Transformation:

        - The Summary section MUST be transformed into Professional Summary.
        - Content MUST describe professional identity and specialization.
        - Content MUST include years of experience with core technologies.
        - Content MUST highlight backend and distributed systems focus.
        - Content MUST mention cloud platforms, processing, and API expertise.

    6.3 Permission Section Transformation:

        - The Permission section SHOULD be simplified for resume context.
        - Content SHOULD state: Permission to share for evaluation, interviews,
          and professional review.
        - This section SHOULD be optional in resume format.

    6.4 Contents Section Transformation:

        - The Contents section MUST be retained.
        - This section reinforces the RFC-compliant structure.
        - Content MUST list all major sections with page references.

    6.5 Document Status to Career Status Transformation:

        - Document Status MUST be renamed to Career Status.
        - Content MUST describe professional capabilities level.
        - Content MUST define focus areas: distributed systems, APIs,
          automation, cloud platforms.
        - Content MUST specify intended audience: engineering teams, technical
          recruiters, system architects.

    6.6 Normative Language to Engineering Principles Transformation:

        - Normative Language MUST be renamed to Engineering Principles.
        - Content MUST replace RFC2119 rules with software engineering
          principles.
        - Content MUST include statements such as:
            - Systems MUST be modular and testable
            - APIs SHOULD be stateless and observable
            - Background processing MUST be fault-tolerant
            - Infrastructure SHOULD be automated
        - This section becomes the engineering philosophy statement.

    6.7 Naming Conventions to Technical Scope Definitions Transformation:

        - Naming Conventions MUST be renamed to Technical Scope Definitions.
        - Content MUST define key technical terms used in the resume.
        - Content MUST include definitions for:
            - Backend System
            - Distributed Processing
            - Worker Pipeline
            - API Integration Layer
            - Automation Tooling
        - This section demonstrates architectural thinking.

    6.8 Structure to Core Competencies Transformation:

        - Structure section MUST be renamed to Core Competencies.
        - Content MUST be organized as system specification subsections.
        - Content MUST include the following subsections:

            6.8.1 Core Languages:
                - Node.js
                - TypeScript
                - JavaScript

            6.8.2 Backend Architecture:
                - NestJS
                - Express
                - Fastify
                - REST APIs
                - Microservices

            6.8.3 Data Systems:
                - PostgreSQL
                - MongoDB
                - Mongoose
                - Sequelize

            6.8.4 Distributed and Background Processing:
                - Worker Threads
                - Queues
                - FFmpeg pipelines
                - Concurrency management

            6.8.5 Cloud and Infrastructure:
                - AWS (S3, Lambda, SNS)
                - Azure
                - Docker
                - Nginx
                - PM2

            6.8.6 Integration and Automation:
                - Payment APIs
